A gas inside a frictionless piston-cylinder system is taken from state $a$ to state $b$ along path $a c b$ (as shown in Figure 3.8). During this reference path, $80 " J"$ of heat flows into the system and the system performs $30 " J"$ of work ($W_{a c b} = -30 " J"$). 

If the system is returned back from state $b$ to state $a$ along a curved path where the work done *on* the system is $20 " J"$, what is the corresponding heat transfer $Q_{b a}$?

